The paper deals with short-term forecasting of gas demand using various machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses statistical properties and relationships with temperature, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques to a real-world problem, which is relevant to the category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
